On September 11, 2019, Vice President Mike Pence delivered remarks at the Flight 93 National Memorial in Shanksville, Pennsylvania to honor the 40 Americans who lost their lives in the plane crash 18 years ago. He spoke about the heroism and sacrifice of the passengers and crew of Flight 93, who fought back against the hijackers and prevented further destruction. Pence also highlighted the importance of remembering and honoring those who lost their lives in the 9/11 attacks, as well as the sacrifices made by the men and women who have served in the armed forces since that day. He emphasized the ongoing threat of terrorism and the resolve of the United States to defend its freedom. Pence concluded his remarks by expressing gratitude to the families of the fallen and promising to always tell their story.